SubType: first trimester placental organ explants grown on matrigel
ClinicalGroup: Dissected mesenchymal villous tissue of early pregnancy was arranged radially on 80 μl drops of growth-factor-reduced Matrigel™ (BD, Bedford, MA) in 24 well plates (SFM; DMEM:Ham's F12 (Gibco) 1:1, supplemented with 100 µg/ml streptomycin/penicillin (Gibco) and incubated for 4 hours at 37°C, 5% CO2 to allow attachment. Wells were then carefully flooded with 500 µl SFM, incubated at 37°C, 5% CO2 and subsequent growth characteristics were monitored by light microscopy. Total RNA or tissue sections were  prepared after 72 hours of incubation.
